A qualitative interpretation of gravimetric data contributed with to information for the inversion of the MT data. A gravimetric feature almost parallel and near the Paran River indicates the presence of an anomalous deep body. We have presented a 2-D geoelectric model of the deep structure in the Paran Basin by processing and inversion of MT data collected in a profile through the central part of the Paran Basin. In this model we verify the presence of a high conductivity band in the upper part, that represents the sedimentary basin and a high resistivity body below the area of the basin. Our model may help to understand the geological structure of the Paran Basin.
